President Biden spoke with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and expressed condemnation for the rocket attacks by Hamas and other terrorist groups, particularly in Jerusalem and Tel Aviv. He reiterated his support for Israel's security and its right to defend itself, while emphasizing the importance of protecting civilians. President Biden also encouraged a pathway towards restoring peace and calm in the region. He discussed the United States' diplomatic engagement with regional countries, including Egypt, Jordan, Qatar, and Palestinian officials. The two leaders agreed to maintain close consultation between their teams and to stay in touch personally in the coming days.